---
import SimpleThemeWrapper from "../components/SimpleThemeWrapper.tsx";
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<meta
			name="google-site-verification"
			content="uyjBT9z6vOnpxn6lM6YnxbI6R4jLSDIAboC8zo1slhM"
		/>
		<meta name="google-adsense-account" content="ca-pub-2444529114040977" />
		<script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-2444529114040977" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
		<link
			rel="icon"
			type="image/png"
			sizes="32x32"
			href="/icon_flex_rail_way_map.png"
		/>
		<link
			rel="icon"
			type="image/png"
			sizes="16x16"
			href="/icon_flex_rail_way_map.png"
		/>
		<link
			rel="apple-touch-icon"
			sizes="180x180"
			href="/icon_flex_rail_way_map.png"
		/>
		<link rel="shortcut icon" href="/icon_flex_rail_way_map.png" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<title>About - フレックス路線図 | 路線図が見にくい・分かりづらいを解決</title>

		<!-- SEO Meta Description -->
		<meta name="description" content="路線図が見にくい・分かりづらいと感じている方へ。フレックス路線図は必要な路線だけを選んで表示できるインタラクティブな路線図サービスです。遅延・運休時にも役立つ見やすい路線図。" />
		<meta name="keywords" content="路線図,見にくい,分かりづらい,分かりにくい,見やすい,シンプル,乗り換え,遅延,運休,鉄道,railway map" />

		<!-- hreflang for multilingual SEO -->
		<link rel="alternate" hreflang="ja" href="https://flex-rail-map.netlify.app/about?lang=ja" />
		<link rel="alternate" hreflang="en" href="https://flex-rail-map.netlify.app/about?lang=en" />
		<link rel="alternate" hreflang="x-default" href="https://flex-rail-map.netlify.app/about" />

		<style>
			body {
				margin: 0;
				padding: 0;
				font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
				transition:
					background-color 0.3s ease,
					color 0.3s ease;
			}
			body.light {
				background-color: #ffffff;
				color: #333333;
			}
			body.dark {
				background-color: #1a1a1a;
				color: #ffffff;
			}
			body.dark h1, body.dark h2, body.dark h3 {
				color: #ffffff;
			}
			body.dark footer {
				background-color: #2d2d2d !important;
				border-top-color: #404040 !important;
				color: #b3b3b3 !important;
			}
			.container {
				max-width: 800px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 20px;
				line-height: 1.6;
			}
			h2 {
				border-bottom: 2px solid #2196F3;
				padding-bottom: 8px;
				margin-bottom: 24px;
			}
			h3 {
				color: #2196F3;
				margin-top: 32px;
				margin-bottom: 12px;
			}
			ul {
				margin-left: 20px;
			}
			li {
				margin-bottom: 8px;
			}
			a {
				color: #2196F3;
				text-decoration: none;
			}
			a:hover {
				text-decoration: underline;
			}
			.back-link {
				display: inline-block;
				margin-bottom: 20px;
				padding: 8px 16px;
				background-color: #2196F3;
				color: white;
				border-radius: 4px;
				text-decoration: none;
			}
			.back-link:hover {
				background-color: #1976D2;
				text-decoration: none;
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<div class="container">
			<a href="/" class="back-link">← 路線図に戻る / Back to Map</a>

			<!-- Japanese About -->
			<div id="about-ja">
				<h2>このサイトについて</h2>

				<h3>サービス概要</h3>
				<p>
				Flex Railway Map は、複雑な鉄道路線図をもっとシンプルに見やすくするためのサービスです。
				通常の乗り換えアプリは便利ですが、遅延や運休があると実際には乗れない電車を案内してしまうことがあります。
				そんなときに路線図を参考にしたくても、ネットで見つかるものは情報が多すぎて読みづらいのが現状です。
				</p>

				<p>
				このサービスでは、必要な路線だけを切り替えて表示できるので、自分にとってわかりやすい路線図をすぐに作れます。
				「今の電車が正しい方向に進んでいるか」「あと何分で乗り換えか」を直感的に確認でき、
				東京に不慣れな人でも安心して移動できます。
				</p>

				<h3>主な機能</h3>
				<ul>
				<li>39路線の東京電車路線（JR、地下鉄、私鉄、新交通システム）</li>
				<li>必要な路線だけの表示切り替え</li>
				<li>駅間の経路検索と所要時間表示</li>
				<li>列車種別による停車駅表示</li>
				<li>日本語・英語の多言語対応</li>
				</ul>

				<h3>技術情報</h3>
				<p>
				React, TypeScript, Astro, Leaflet を使用して構築され、Netlify にデプロイされています。
				Claude Code を活用して段階的に機能を追加しています。
				</p>

				<h3>開発者</h3>
				<p>
				Developed by ema | <a href="https://github.com/emar27181">GitHub: emar27181</a>
				</p>
			</div>

			<!-- English About -->
			<div id="about-en" style="display: none;">
				<h2>About This Site</h2>

				<h3>Service Overview</h3>
				<p>
				Flex Railway Map is a service that makes complex railway maps simple and easy to read.
				Regular route planner apps are useful, but they sometimes suggest trains that are delayed or not running.
				Existing online railway maps contain too much information and are difficult to read.
				</p>

				<p>
				With this service, you can switch on and off only the routes you need, creating a custom simplified map that fits your situation.
				You can quickly check if your train is heading in the right direction or estimate how many minutes remain until your transfer.
				Even if you're not familiar with Tokyo, this tool helps you travel with confidence.
				</p>

				<h3>Key Features</h3>
				<ul>
				<li>39 Tokyo railway lines (JR, subway, private railways, new transit systems)</li>
				<li>Toggle display of only needed routes</li>
				<li>Route search and travel time display between stations</li>
				<li>Station display by train type</li>
				<li>Japanese and English language support</li>
				</ul>

				<h3>Technical Information</h3>
				<p>
				Built with React, TypeScript, Astro, and Leaflet, deployed on Netlify.
				Development is supported by Claude Code to incrementally add new features.
				</p>

				<h3>Developer</h3>
				<p>
				Developed by ema | <a href="https://github.com/emar27181">GitHub: emar27181</a>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<script>
			// Language detection and switching
			function switchLanguage() {
				const urlParams = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
				const lang = urlParams.get('lang') || 'ja'; // Default to Japanese

				const jaContent = document.getElementById('about-ja');
				const enContent = document.getElementById('about-en');

				if (lang === 'en') {
					jaContent.style.display = 'none';
					enContent.style.display = 'block';
				} else {
					jaContent.style.display = 'block';
					enContent.style.display = 'none';
				}
			}

			// Apply theme
			function applyTheme() {
				const savedTheme = localStorage.getItem('theme') || 'light';
				document.body.className = savedTheme;
			}

			// Initialize on page load
			document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
				switchLanguage();
				applyTheme();
			});
		</script>

		<SimpleThemeWrapper client:only="react" />
	</body>
</html>